# **Fueling Your Emotions Through Empowering Beliefs**

Many people live under the tyranny of their emotions because they are unaware of their mindset. Not all your emotions are driven by your mindset, but your mindset does powerfully affect your emotions.

## **An Easy Exercise to Fuel Your Emotions**

If you doubt me, test it by spending a few minutes focusing on all the mistakes you've made this past week and what a horrible person you are. Don’t be surprised if your emotions spiral downward.

But before you get lost in that pit, start thinking about what you've done right and the things you're grateful for this week. It may take some time, but soon you will find your emotions climbing upward.

Unless you take charge of your thoughts, you will live under the tyranny of your emotions.

## **A New Perspective on Emotions**

Most people, when they find themselves getting anxious or angry, immediately begin looking for things to change in their situation. 

Successful people, however, pause and step back to look at the bigger picture.

Ask yourself, "What am I thinking? What mindset is powering these emotions?"

I usually take a few moments to think about it and probe a bit. Sometimes the answer is immediately obvious. Sometimes it comes the next day or the next week. Sometimes it doesn’t come for months or years, but it always come.

Remember how your mindsets are like the engine powering your life? Well, emotions are like the gauges and lights informing you about what is going on under the hood. If the bells are ringing and lights flashing, most likely something needs repaired.

When you begin repairing your mindsets, you open the door to transformation (and a better ride).

If you learn to manage your mindset, you'll learn to manage your emotions.
